  "original_title": "\u0b95\u0bca\u0bb4\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1 \u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0ba9 \u0b8e\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Fuel ships arriving in Colombo",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Power and Energy Minister Kanchana Wijesekara said today (11) that three fuel tankers will arrive in the country this week.",
        "Accordingly, he said that a diesel ship will arrive between tomorrow (12th) and 15th, a heavy oil ship between 14th and 16th of this month, and a lubricating oil ship between 15th and 17th of this month.",
        "He also pointed out that complete payments were made to the Lanka IOC last Friday with the help of the Central Bank of Sri Lanka and the Ministry of Finance.",
        "He also mentioned that the diesel batch will arrive in the country between July 15 and 17 and the petrol batch between July 22 and 24.",
        "He also mentioned that advance payment was made last week for diesel to arrive between 15th to 17th and petrol to arrive between 17th to 19th last week and the excess amount for diesel will be paid today (11).",
        "He mentioned that the diesel batch that was due to arrive on July 9 was delayed due to inclement weather, and that the departure of the fuel from India this morning (11) has been confirmed and will arrive at Colombo port between July 12 and 15."
      ],
